ef6000SysAdmStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the switch. A management station may place the switch in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The desired administrative status are online(1) and offline(2). ef6000FruStatus.description: This object identifies the operational status of the module. The active(1) state indicates that the current module is active; The backup(2) state indicates that the back up module is used; The update-busy (3) state indicates that the module is in the updating process; The failed(4) state indicates that the current module is failed.

ef6000PortAdmStatus.description: The desired state of the port. A management station may place the port in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The testing(3) state indicates that no user frames can be passed. As the result of either explicit management action or per configuration information accessible by the switch, ef6000PortAdmStatus is then changed to either the online(1) or testing(3) states, or remains in the offline state.

ef6000PortBindingTable.name: ef6000PortBindingTable

ef6000PortBindingEntry.description: An entry containing the port binding information of the switch port.

ef6000PortBindingIndex.description: The fixed physical port number on the switch. It ranges from 1 to the number of physical ports that can be supported in the switch.

ef6000PortBindingFlag.name: ef6000PortBindingFlag
ef6000PortBindingFlag.description: The flag indicates whether or not Port Binding is in effect for an individual port.

ef6000PortConfiguredWWN.name: ef6000PortConfiguredWWN
ef6000PortConfiguredWWN.description: The authorized port WWN for attached servers and storage systems (F ports), or the authorized switch WWN for attached switches (E ports).

ef6000PortAttachedWWN.name: ef6000PortAttachedWWN
ef6000PortAttachedWWN.description: The WWN of the device currently attached to the port whether it has successfully connected or is currently being rejected due to a Port Binding violation.

ef6000ActiveZoneSetName.name: ef6000ActiveZoneSetName
ef6000ActiveZoneSetName.description: The active zone set name. This value will return NULL if the active zone set state is disabled

ef6000ActiveZoneCount.name: ef6000ActiveZoneCount
ef6000ActiveZoneCount.description: The number of zones in the active zone set. This value will return 0 if the active zone set state is disabled

ef6000DefaultZoneSetState.name: ef6000DefaultZoneSetState
ef6000DefaultZoneSetState.description: The set state of the default zone set (1=Enabled,2= Disabled).

ef6000ActiveZoneSetState.name: ef6000ActiveZoneSetState
ef6000ActiveZoneSetState.description: The state of the active zone set. If the active zone set state is disabled, then ActiveZoneSetName and ActiveZoneSetCount are invalid (1=Enabled,2= Disabled).

ef6000HardwareEnforcedZoning.name: ef6000HardwareEnforcedZoning
ef6000HardwareEnforcedZoning.description: Indicates if zoning is hardware enforced (1=Yes, 2=No).

ef6000ActiveZoneTable.name: ef6000ActiveZoneTable
ef6000ActiveZoneTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each zone in the active zone set.

ef6000ActiveZoneEntry.name: ef6000ActiveZoneEntry
ef6000ActiveZoneEntry.description: An entry containing the information specific to a zone.

ef6000ZoneIndex.name: ef6000ZoneIndex
ef6000ZoneIndex.description: Zone index number. This number will range from 1 to the number of zones specified by the ActiveZoneCount.

ef6000ZoneName.name: ef6000ZoneName
ef6000ZoneName.description: This object is the name of this zone entry.

ef6000ZoneMemberCount.name: ef6000ZoneMemberCount
ef6000ZoneMemberCount.description: This object contains a count of the number of members in this zone entry.

ef6000ActiveMemberTable.name: ef6000ActiveMemberTable
ef6000ActiveMemberTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each member in the active zone set.

ef6000ActiveMemberEntry.name: ef6000ActiveMemberEntry
ef6000ActiveMemberEntry.description: An entry containing the information specific to a member.

ef6000MemberZoneIndex.name: ef6000MemberZoneIndex
ef6000MemberZoneIndex.description: The index of the zone that this member belongs to. This is the same value as ef6000ZoneIndex.

ef6000MemberIndex.name: ef6000MemberIndex
ef6000MemberIndex.description: Member index number. This number will range from 1 to the number of members specified by the corresponding ZoneMemberCount.

ef6000MemberType.name: ef6000MemberType
ef6000MemberType.description: This object is the type of addressing that is associated with this member.

ef6000MemberWWN.name: ef6000MemberWWN
ef6000MemberWWN.description: The WWN name as an 8-octet string. This value is only valid if the member type is 1, otherwise it will return all zeros.

ef6000MemberDomainID.name: ef6000MemberDomainID
ef6000MemberDomainID.description: The domain ID. This value is only valid if the member type is 2, otherwise it will return NULL.

ef6000MemberPortNumber.name: ef6000MemberPortNumber
ef6000MemberPortNumber.description: The port number. This value is only valid if the member type is 2, otherwise it will return NULL.

ef6000TATable.name: ef6000TATable
ef6000TATable.description: A table that contains one entry for each configured threshold alert.

ef6000TAEntry.name: ef6000TAEntry
ef6000TAEntry.description: An entry containing a threshold alert configuration.

ef6000TAIndex.name: ef6000TAIndex
ef6000TAIndex.description: This object is used to identify which threshold has been triggered.

ef6000TAState.name: ef6000TAState
ef6000TAState.description: The current state of the threshold.

ef6000TAPortType.name: ef6000TAPortType
ef6000TAPortType.description: A threshold can be set on a list of physical port numbers or on all the ports of the specified type (ePorts, fPorts).

ef6000TAPortList.name: ef6000TAPortList
ef6000TAPortList.description: A bit map that identifies which ports this threhold alert applies to (only valid if the Threshold Alert Port Type = list). The left most bit represents the port 0.

ef6000TAInterval.name: ef6000TAInterval
ef6000TAInterval.description: The number of minutes in a threshold alert interval.

ef6000TATriggerValue.name: ef6000TATriggerValue
ef6000TATriggerValue.description: If the alert type is a Throughput Threshold Alert, then this is the percent utilization (1-100) required to trigger an alert. If the alert type is a Counter Threshold Alert, then this is the counter delta required to trigger an alert.

ef6000TTADirection.name: ef6000TTADirection
ef6000TTADirection.description: This only applies when the alert type is a Throughput Threshold Alert. It specifies the throughput direction of the threshold.

ef6000TTATriggerDuration.name: ef6000TTATriggerDuration
ef6000TTATriggerDuration.description: This only applies when the alert type is a Throughput Threshold Alert. It specifies the amount of time during a threshold alert interval that the trigger must be exceeded before an alert is generated.

ef6000CTACounter.name: ef6000CTACounter
ef6000CTACounter.description: This only applies when the alert type is a Counter Threshold Alert. It specifies statistical counter or counter set to be monitored. (This object is not supported in the current release.)

ef6000PortScn.name: ef6000PortScn
ef6000PortScn.description: An ef6000PortScn(1) is generated whenever a Fc_Port changes its operational state. For instance, the Fc_Port goes from on-line to offline.

ef6000FruScn.name: ef6000FruScn
ef6000FruScn.description: An ef6000FruScn(2) is generated whenever a FRU status changes its operational state.

ef6000PortBindingViolation.name: ef6000PortBindingViolation
ef6000PortBindingViolation.description: An ef6000PortBindingViolation(3) is generated whenever the switch detects that a port binding violation occurs.

ef6000ThresholdAlert.name: ef6000ThresholdAlert
ef6000ThresholdAlert.description: An ef6000ThresholdAlert(4) is generated whenever a threshold alert occurs.
